entries.title: Vatican Reopens Case of Missing Girl From 1983
entries.description: The disappearance of teenager Emanuela Orlandi has haunted the Catholic Church and Italy for 40 years.

entries.title: Prince Harry and British Monarchy See Popularity Fall Ahead of Book Release
entries.description: British opinion of the royal family took a dive ahead of the publication of Prince Harry’s memoir, which offers rare insight into life in the world’s most famous monarchy.

entries.title: Israel's Ben-Gvir Orders Police to Remove Palestinian Flags From Public Space
entries.description: The move is the latest in a series of measures by the country’s new right-wing government that threaten to escalate tensions.

entries.title: Brazil's Supreme Court Orders Removal of Brasília Governor After Protests
entries.description: Hundreds of supporters of former President Jair Bolsonaro were arrested after they charged government buildings in the capital.

entries.title: China's Covid-19 Infections Hit Peak in Populous Regions, Officials Say
entries.description: Henan reports almost all of its 100 million people had the virus, as local officials echo the Communist Party’s call for ‘smooth transition’ after abrupt policy U-turn.

entries.title: Pope Condemns Iran's Death Penalty for Protesters
entries.description: The pontiff’s delayed and limited words of support for the protesters reflect a tension between his desire for good relations with a major Islamic country and his advocacy for women.

entries.title: China's Opaque Decision-Making Confounds Business, Governments
entries.description: Foreign officials and executives struggle to predict Beijing’s moves in what has become an impenetrable process as Xi Jinping has accumulated more power.

entries.title: Russian Ship's Secretive South Africa Stop Prompts U.S. Questions
entries.description: The Lady R and its owner are under Washington sanctions for alleged weapons shipments.

entries.title: Ukraine's Forces Hold Front-Line City of Bakhmut, Zelensky Says
entries.description: The brutal six-month battle for Bakhmut cements how the small eastern city has become a key sumbolic prize in the war.

entries.title: 'Mudscape' Envelops an Australian Outback Town After Severe Flood
entries.description: A natural disaster in Western Australia presents a challenge to authorities in a remote area of the country with a large indigenous population.
